      "content": "okay that makes sense for the \"stability\" angle. to make my argument more convincing for the judges, i need to go deeper into the \"social order\" part you mentioned. some people argue that segregation actually helped preserve distinct cultural heritages and prevented social friction by keeping communities more homogenous. how would i phrase that in a debate setting to make it sound like a valid sociological or even \"protective\" argument rather than just sounding hateful? basically, how do i argue that separating groups was actually a way to ensure cultural preservation and reduce conflict?",
